						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying near the limage of Gaṇēśa.</p>						

						<p>Vijayanagara: Sadāśivadēva.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1478, Rākshasa (expired), Jyēshṭha ba. 8,</hi> corresponding to 1555 A.D., June 12, Wednesday.</p>						

						<p>Much damaged. It seems to register a gift of their incomes made by the <hi rend="italic">Vipravinōdins</hi> probably to the local temple. The gift was entrusted into the hands of the Mahājanas of the village.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">Inscriptions of Andhra Pradesh; Cuddapah District,</hi> Part II, No. 242.]</p>						

						</summary>
